JO  - AMJ
SP  - 504
EP  - 521
VL  - 38
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Relief services provided by corporations to employees following a natural disaster were expected to be associated with reduced levels of employee strains. Data from 143 hurricane victims partially supported this prediction, revealing that tangible support meeting employees' primary needs had the most numerous effects over the course of the disaster aftermath.
